-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Backfill tms_route_stop.evening_time from the JKKN "BUS STOPING TIMEING" sheet.
--
-- Generated from the workbook using the project's own parse-route-workbook +
-- normalize-time logic, so the values match what the route importer would write.
-- Matched to existing stops by (tms_route.route_code = sheet name) + sequence_order,
-- which line up 1:1 (verified: per-route DB stop counts == parsed stop counts, and a
-- (route_code, seq) → stop_name diff against the live table returned 0 mismatches).
-- Updates ONLY evening_time; route 01 (manual, not in the sheet) is left NULL.
--
-- A few evening cells in the source sheet are typo'd (e.g. an evening value that reads
-- as a morning time); those are imported verbatim — the same best-effort behaviour as
-- the importer — and can be corrected via the admin route edit form.
--
-- Idempotent: re-running just rewrites the same evening_time values.
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

update public.tms_route_stop s
set evening_time = v.evening_time::time
from (values
